<br>
Far-sighted, short-sighted...which is it? Given there is information they know that we dot, how does withholding that information better equip the population to make an educated decision? It doesn't... It could be truth or hearsay. But none the less we make major changes to try and protect against every possibility. If I turned left this morning instead of turning right, I may have been in a auto accident. What I need is a crystal ball so I will know for sure.<br>
<br>
We cannot have freedom and security co-exist at the same time. One will give way to the other. Freedom to me means alot more then driving to work, collecting a paycheck, driving home and sitting in front of my TV or computer. Freedom to me means I can travel this country completely un-obstructed, not having to stop at military check-points, not having to maintain a national ID card, not being monitored, questioned, suspected, considered, verified, screened, checked, inspected, detected, and rejected. When ones only &quot;passport&quot; to freedom is that they &quot;haven't done anything wrong&quot;, one has a passport that can be revoked.<br>
<br>
Suspicion has its place and use. However, one could have been considered on the verge of a hate crime if they would have suspiciously discriminated against the terrorist who were taking flight training classes. &quot;I feel like those A-rabs are up to no good!&quot;... you prejudice bastard! How dare you stereotype those nice middle-eastern men. What have they done to you???&quot;<br>
<br>
...the fix..?   Make everyone a suspect. Black, white, Indian, middle-eastern, Hispanic, Jewish, German...put every American under the microscope....even adjust the laws so that the military to take action against the population.<br>
<br>
How about this.. how about before they give the military such unprecedented, although regulated, power over the population, we make them tell us exactly why!  Not speculate, formulate, calculate, and fabricate....give us facts as to why 'We The People' should let such a thing take place in OUR country!<br>
<br>
What we do not know CAN hurt us...we know that. But let not what we do not know be used against us. Mr. Bush, please have a foresight of freedom (the way it was intended to be), not a foresight of fear.<br>
<br>
Yours truly suffering… from a severely dimpled chad,<br>
